casebody.data:
STATE of Missouri, Respondent,
v.
William Kody ZABRISKIE, Appellant. WD 79677 Missouri Court of Appeals, Western District. ORDER FILED: October 30, 2018 Shaun Mackelprang, Jefferson City, MO, for respondent. Jedd C. Schneider, Columbia, MO, for appellant. Before Division Three: Gary D. Witt, Presiding Judge, Cynthia L. Martin, Judge and Anthony Rex Gabbert, Judge

ORDER

Per curiam:

Appellant William Zabriskie ("Zabriskie") appeals his conviction of the class C felony of possession of a controlled substance, section 195.202, following a jury trial in the circuit court of Henry County, Missouri. Zabriskie was sentenced to eight years' imprisonment as a prior offender. On appeal, Zabriskie alleges that there was insufficient evidence to find that he possessed the methamphetamine in question. We affirm. Rule 30.25(b).
